<b>Not too bad of a song. - </b>4/28/01 10:20:45 PM<br>~ <b>Ensis Arament</b><blockquote>I'm still using this song, and I'm level 47.  Usually when you get this high, you're often grouping with Shamen or Enchanters--Both which usually handle the hasting instead of you, since they're better at it.  This gives you another spot to open up for songs.  Sometimes I actually have trouble filling it up, can't decide between which songs to pick.  In the end, this is usually one of the first I choose.  Though small when sung, it's a decent buff amount.  Throw in a drum and a couple of the DoT Chants and you've got a pretty good twist.<br><br>It does NOT stack with Guardian Rythms (Level 17), Anthem De Arms (Level 10), Johnathon's Provication (Level 45) or Berserker Cresendo (Level 42).  However, Guardian and Berserker both do stack for the AC bonus.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
