<b>Level 36... try level 50... :) - </b>2/15/01 4:48:50 PM<br>~ <b>Gaedan Mentheren</b><blockquote>At level 50, when you recieve the ultimate group melee buff, Verses of Victory, I do believe that Chant of Battle, your &quot;lowly&quot; level one song, will also keep pace with Verses, resulting in the Ultimate STR & DEX buff.  While the effects of the stat boosts can be debated, in a tank-heavy group where your melee damage can be negliable, try pulling out your drums and seeing how much your warriors will crit, proc, and how much their damage will be increased.<br><br>Definately a song that earns its wings later in life.<br><br>(Also, try using this with a drum while smithing, or helping a friend smith.  The DEX and STR will be huge boon to their metal-crafting efforts.)</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Have weapons with special procs? - </b>1/28/01 3:06:19 AM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>Just because this is the very first song you get as a bard doesn't mean its the first you'll put away. Ask your group whether they have special weapons with proc effects. If so, they may like you to play this song to boost dexterity so the weapon procs more frequently.This song does NOT stack with Anthem (level 10), so determine whether your group would rather have haste or a dex boost.<br><br>If your group already has a haste buff, you can put Anthem away, and use the DEX, STR, AC boost from this song. Once you hit level 36, you will get a Haste song that DOES stack with Chant of Battle, giving a very nice group STR, DEX, AGI, and haste boost.</blockquote></td></tr></table></blockquote><br><br><br><br><br><br><a href="/songs.asp?&song=1">Back to Normal Mode</a><br><br><br><i>Printed from EQDiva.com on 8/21/03 6:50:50 PM.</i><br><br></td></tr></table>
